commit.message: Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/taylorfutral/SlugCycle
Switched the number back over to Taylor for the Inboard meeting.
Updated SMS entries
Replaced the current location icon with a gold star.

Got distance function working. SMS alerts now give you distance
in feet.

Got a very simple info window working.

No data entry yet, but clicking on a marker now opens a window above
with our Meteor template rendered into it. The window switches from one
marker to another automatically and closes when no marker is selected.
Minor CSS/HTML adjustments.
Got started on the marker editor. Also fixed some bugs with moving events around.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/taylorfutral/SlugCycle
Kevin: Changed the toolbar to work with Dustin's new header.
Added logo to the top of HTML file
HTML/CSS Changes
android should work now
I added a Pebble app to explain SlugCycle use procedure.

Added a few more event hooks and got removing events
to work.

Fixed the SMS code to post to Taylor's Pebble watch.
Also fixed the distance function so it returns an
actual number (still needs unit conversion, but it works).

Just got TextBelt SMS working. There's now a server-side
method that can send SMS messages to any number. We'll
use this to get notifications to the Pebble and possibly
do real-time phone-to-Pebble communication this way.
Added the ability to switch tools.

Added Bacon.js for event streaming, reworked the map template to
use event streams. Map now centers on the user's position automatically
, but only while the user is moving.

Added Bootstrap and started doing minor layout

Basically I just added a sidebar on the left (buttons don't do anything
yet) and put the map div in a column instead of letting it take up the
whole screen.

Missed a file.

Waypoints have their own definition file, they don't need to be in the
main file.

Added the ability to put markers on the map.

Markers are stored in the Waypoint collection and are persistent. They
should also be changeable from multiple computers, but I haven't tested
that yet. Also added my API key to the project.

Added geolocation support. The map auto-centers on the user's
current location and places a marker on it.
Adding a Google maps template. Not tested yet. Hope it works!

Initial Commit: Just a default Meteor app with the
Google Map API package added.
